{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads to wake up to collect the data."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a thread calls "},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now, it will wait until","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has called "},{"code":"push_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"race between the check of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"text":" by the while loop in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also important to use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"true.  See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"type":"text","text":" for an explanation of why the condition may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"code":"g_cond_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on it and "},{"code":"g_cond_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when done.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol"],"traits":